                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Baker</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-06-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 18, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of this date, stating that the provisional Government of Salvador
                    informs you that the President of the United States has recognized that
                    Government and now asks extradition refugees, has been received. No such action
                    has been taken by the President. You will be governed by Mr. Gresham’s
                    instruction in telegram to you of June 12 until directed further by this
                    Department. Later reply as to Nicaragua.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
